    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ULSCH decoding data completion before return\n\n### Summary\nThe `ulsch_decoding_data()` function in the LTE ULSCH decoder was returning immediately after submitting decoding tasks to the thread pool, without waiting for the actual decoding to complete. This caused unexpected behavior for callers who expected the function to complete the decoding before returning control.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident when directly calling `ulsch_decoding_data()` where the function would return before any of the turbo decoding segments were processed, leading to incomplete or corrupted data in the HARQ buffers.\n\nThe fix modifies the `ulsch_decoding_data()` function to wait for all submitted decoding tasks to complete before returning, ensuring that the decoded data is available when the function returns.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/ulsch_decoding.c`: Modified `ulsch_decoding_data()` to wait for completion of all decoding tasks before returning\n  - Added local counter to track submitted tasks\n  - Added waiting loop that pulls responses from thread pool until all tasks complete\n  - Properly manages the global `proc->nbDecode` counter\n  - Ensures unique task identification by using segment index in task keys\n\n"
}